  "root": "sprites",
  "_note": "Authored 2026-07-13 by standard/author-simcit.mjs FROM THE ENGINE. SimCit is micropolisJS (a GPL'd Micropolis/SimCity port). Most of its art is a TILESET baked into base64 data URIs and is not sheet art; what is fetchable on disk is sprites/ — the moving objects. The whole contract is one line, src/baseSprite.js:93: ['obj', this.type, '-', this.frame - 1].join('') — so the key is obj<type>-<frame-1> and `type` is a SPRITE_* constant. The SPRITE_* set is therefore the complete set of art the engine can reach. kind is `catalog`: per GENRE_MOVESETS, a city-builder has no character anim bar — the audit is state-variant completeness, not a moveset. These frames are headings/cells of an object.",
  "_knownGap": {
    "what": "4 sprite frames on disk for a type the engine DOES NOT HAVE. spriteConstants.ts defines 7 types (train, helicopter, airplane, ship, monster, tornado, explosion); there is no 8th. Nothing in the engine can compose the key \"obj8-*\", so this art is unreachable by construction. Do NOT fix this by declaring an 8th type the game cannot instantiate — either the engine gains the type, or the art is archived.",
    "files": [
      "obj8-0.png",
      "obj8-1.png",
      "obj8-2.png",
      "obj8-3.png"
    ]
  },
  "mechanics": {
    "_note": "No actors. A city-builder animates objects and tiles, not characters."
  },
